hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I live in London healthslate.com Gates was the one who rather recently appointed Ray Ozzie as Microsoft CTO. The decision, it is said, was largely due to one nostalgic conversation where they enjoyed reminiscing over antiquated CP/M programming. It was just the same old Bill Gates whim and whimsy that had nothing to do with the company’s real strategic needs, the same mindset that has hobbled its chances since he tried to take over the Internet and then quickly lost interest.
